{
  "texts": [
    "Large language models are computational devices used for natural language processing.",
    "These models are able to generate human-like text, answer questions, and complete other language-related tasks with high accuracy (Kasneci et al., 2023).",
    "In this article I consider ChatGPT as the most notable example of a LLM, although my 2023; Hernández-Orallo and Vold 2019",
    "This issue is out of the scope of this treatment but is worth mentioning if we want to educate students not simply as epistemic agents but as whole human beings.",
    "Footnote 7 (Continued) arguments can be extended to other LLMs."
  ]
}